💡 CÓMO FUNCIONA CAPA 2

Progressive Disclosure (3-Layer Pattern):

┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Session N+1 Starts                                         │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                        ↓
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Layer 1: SEARCH (Index)                                    │
│ claude-mem.search("relevant keywords")                     │
│ Returns: Top 5 observations metadata (IDs + timestamps)    │
│ Tokens: ~50-100                                            │
│ Cost: Minimal                                              │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                        ↓
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Layer 2: TIMELINE (Context)                                │
│ If relevant, fetch timeline around interesting results     │
│ Shows: 3 chronological entries for context                 │
│ Tokens: ~100-200                                           │
│ Cost: Low                                                  │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                        ↓
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Layer 3: FULL OBSERVATIONS (On-Demand)                     │
│ Only if explicitly needed: get_observations(IDs)           │
│ Returns: Complete narratives and decisions                 │
│ Tokens: ~300-500 per observation (lazy-loaded)             │
│ Cost: Only when needed                                     │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Result: Typical Session N+1 injection = 150-450 tokens
        Without memory, manual context = 5,000-10,000 tokens
        Savings: ~95%

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

🔧 CONFIGURACIÓN EXPLICADA

Model Selection:
  "model": "sonnet"  // NOT opus
  → Sonnet es más eficiente para compresión
  → 50% más barato que opus
  → Suficiente para tareas de memory distillation

Progressive Disclosure:
  "progressiveDisclosure": true
  "maxSearchResults": 5
  "maxTimelineResults": 3
  → Lazy-load instead of all-at-once
  → Top 5 most relevant observations
  → Timeline for context (3 entries)

Vector Search Tuning:
  "search_ef": 50  // Default is 200
  → Más rápido (balance velocidad/precisión)
  → Trade-off: 95% recall vs 98% pero 4x más rápido
  → Para sesiones futuras es aceptable

Tool Exclusion:
  "CLAUDE_MEM_SKIP_TOOLS": "ListMcpResourcesTool,Skill,Notification"
  → No capturar ruido de framework
  → Capturar: Edit, Write, Read, Bash, WebFetch (domain logic)

Auto-Cleanup:
  "retentionDays": 90
  "autoCleanup": true
  → Keep 90 days of observations
  → Auto-delete older entries
  → Previene crecimiento unbounded (~30-50MB steady state)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

⚠️ IMPORTANTE: Observaciones de Claude

Claude-mem captura automáticamente TODAS tus acciones vía hooks:

Captured Automatically:
  ✓ PostToolUse:Edit   — File edits
  ✓ PostToolUse:Write  — File writes
  ✓ UserPromptSubmit   — What you asked
  ✓ SessionStart       — Session boundaries
  ✓ Bash, WebFetch, etc. — Explorations

NOT Captured (by design):
  ✗ List operations (noisy framework stuff)
  ✗ Skill invocations (meta overhead)
  ✗ Notifications (environment, not decisions)

Result: Memory = your actual work + decisions, not noise

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

📊 STORAGE IMPACT

Current Size:  ~12MB (initialized, will grow after Session N use)
Per Month:     ~10-20MB (depending on activity)
Retention:     90 days = ~30-50MB steady state
Auto-Cleanup:  Deletes observations older than 90 days

Backup:
  cp -r ~/.claude-mem ~/.claude-mem.backup

No action needed - auto-cleanup keeps it bounded.

